1 (a) Review the submittal for compliance with the provisions of sections 49 to 59, chapter 110,
2 Oregon Laws 2024.
3 (b)(A) If the submittal substantially complies with the provisions of sections 49 to 59, chapter
4 110, Oregon Laws 2024, issue an order approving the submittal; or
5 (B) If the submittal does not substantially comply with the provisions of sections 49 to 59,
6 chapter 110, Oregon Laws 2024, issue an order remanding the submittal to the city or to Metro with
7 a specific determination of deficiencies in the submittal and with sufficient detail to identify a spe-
8 cific remedy for any deficiency in a subsequent resubmittal.
9 (3) If a conceptual plan is remanded to Metro under subsection (2)(b) of this section:
10 (a) The department shall notify the city; and
11 (b) The city may amend its conceptual plan and resubmit a petition to Metro under section 51,
12 chapter 110, Oregon Laws 2024.
13 (4) Judicial review of the department’s order:
14 (a) Must be as a review of orders other than a contested case under ORS 183.484; and
15 (b) May be initiated only by the city or an owner of a proposed site that was submitted to the
16 department.
17 (5) Following the approval of a submittal under this section, a local government must include
18 the added lands in any future inventory of buildable lands or determination of housing capacity
19 under ORS 197A.270, 197A.280, 197A.335 or 197A.350.
